{
  "texts": [
    "If the product of dt ðn + 1Þ dt ðnÞ Jacobians is naively defined, the amplitude of this gradient might vanish or explode exponentially fast as the number of layers becomes large.",
    "To calculate analytically the Jacobian of the SNN, we define a diagonal matrix M (n) with elements M ðnÞ ij = δ ij Hðt ðnÞ max À t ðnÞ i Þ that are 1 if and only if spike t ðnÞ i occurs before t ðnÞ max.",
    "The Jacobian of the network can then be written as (⋅ is the matrix multiplication), see section \"Methods\" for calculations:",
    "where the matrix B (n) is the diagonal matrix with elements B ðnÞ i.",
    "From the exact reverse mapping, we know that the diagonal matrix M acts like a binary mask with elements M ðnÞ ii = 1 if and only if the equivalent ReLU unit i in layer n has a non-zero output."
  ]
}